The implementation is complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented:

**`ColumnParallelLinear`**: Splits the weight matrix by columns (dim=1), so each rank gets `(out_features, in_features/world_size)`. The forward pass computes `x @ weight.T` producing `(batch, out_features)`, then uses `all_gather` + `cat` to concatenate outputs across ranks along the last dimension. Bias is full-size (`out_features`) on each rank.

**`RowParallelLinear`**: Splits the weight matrix by rows (dim=0), so each rank gets `(out_features/world_size, in_features)`. The forward pass computes `x @ weight.T` producing `(batch, out_features/world_size)`, then uses `all_reduce` (SUM) to sum partial outputs across ranks. Bias is full-size (`out_features`) on each rank.

Both classes were verified to produce correct results matching the reference (unsharded) linear layer output at world_size=1.

